KW  - S-curve
KW  - Stochastic general equilibrium model
KW  - Terms of trade
KW  - Trade balance dynamics
AB  - In their analysis of the dynamic behavior of terms of trade and the trade balance, Backus, Kehoe, and Kydland found that the lead and lag correlation between these two variables is S-shaped for a set of OECD countries. Furthermore, they show that this S-curve can be replicated by a two-country dynamic general equilibrium model. Surprisingly, the S-curve also describes the dynamic relationship between terms of trade and the trade balance for a large set of LDCs. This S-curve can also be reproduced by a small-open-economy model which captures some important features of LDC economies. The S-curve is unexpectedly robust to variations in the key parameters of the model. The model also captures the business cycle properties of the LDC data.
ER  - 

